description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We are recruiting a team of Healthcare Assistants to support a lovely baby girl with her complex care needs.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are committed, motivated, enjoy delivering one to one support and can build positive relationships with our service users and their families, this could be just the position you are looking for!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our service user is currently residing in Royal Manchester Children&#39;s hospital and we are working hard to get her home to her loving family, to do this she needs a fantastic care team in place.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;She is a very happy girl who loves to watch Moana and Monsters inc.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for people who have a genuine interest in working with children and can commit to joining her team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;You may at times be required to attend RMCH for some aspects of her clinical training, but this will mainly be conducted at her family home in Lytham St Anne’s&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We offer comprehensive training allowing you to enhance your experience of working in care and or with children by working in a more clinical role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a great opportunity where you will be using your valuable skills from your gained experience and progressing into a Children’s Complex Care Assistant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Experience Required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* 6 months previous care experience &lt;br /&gt;* Medication Administration &lt;br /&gt;* Personal Care &lt;br /&gt;* Moving and Handling&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Tracheostomy Care &lt;br /&gt;* Ventilation Management &lt;br /&gt;* Gastrostomy Care (Peg Feeding)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have the following shifts available;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;* Night shifts available from 21:00 - 07:00&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is a personally rewarding role where you can build on your clinical skills and experience, whilst you will be delivering exceptional care and support to our service user and her family.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why work for Apollo Home Healthcare?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We specialise in the provision of highly complex clinical care services delivered in the homes of service users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are passionate about delivering the highest standard of care and we recognise that our Nurses, Healthcare Assistants and Support Workers are integral to doing this. In return for your hard work and dedication you will receive:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible hours to suit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confirmed rotas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent rates of pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Holiday pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full clinical training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to work with other service users in the area&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ongoing professional training and development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need key workers on the front line supporting our service users in the fight against the COVID-19 Pandemic.&lt;/p&gt;
